fields.label_text: ANONYMOUS (Iconography and Religions). A series of connected disks of paper cut from one sheet, illustrating missionary subjects, German, 18th century; and a series of connected disks of paper, with English translations of the inscriptions on the engraved disks, the whole contained in a metal box, one half of which is a cast of an 18th-century German medal, the other half, a cast of a 19th-century medallion, possibly Italian in origin. The metal box contains two more engraved medallions as lining, and is itself contained in a shagreen case. Etchings, coloured by hand. Size of sheet (10 x 5 3/4). Diam. of metal box (1 3/4.) E.2128-1930. Given by Mr. Donald Gunn.
